ment that the founding fathers fought in order to preserve their right to enslave others. The Counter-Revolution of 1776 brings us to a radical new understanding of the traditional heroic creation myth of the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican AmericansxHistoryyTo 1863. 0aAntislavery movementszUnited StatesxHistoryy18th century. 0aSlaveryzUnited StatesxHistoryy18th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / Revolutionary Period (1775-1800).2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479874972.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479874972423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479874972/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles